---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use - FemRes"
  description="Understand the terms and conditions for using the FemRes platform."
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
      <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none dark:prose-invert">
        <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Last Updated: September 2025</p>

        <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>Welcome to FemRes! By accessing or using our website and services, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our services.</p>

        <h2>2. Service Description</h2>
        <p>FemRes is a feminist content aggregation platform that aims to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide high-quality feminist-related content (books, articles, videos, podcasts, academic papers)</li>
          <li>Offer diverse content through AI-driven curation and community collaboration</li>
          <li>Promote the spread and discussion of feminist thought</li>
          <li>Provide personalized content recommendations for users</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. User Responsibilities</h2>
        <h3>3.1 Account Responsibilities</h3>
        <p>You are responsible for:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Providing accurate registration information</li>
          <li>Protecting your account security</li>
          <li>Keeping your information up to date</li>
          <li>All activities under your account</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2 Content Contributions</h3>
        <p>When contributing content to the platform, you must:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Ensure content is accurate, relevant, and valuable</li>
          <li>Respect others' intellectual property rights</li>
          <li>Provide accurate source information</li>
          <li>Follow our content quality standards</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Prohibited Conduct</h2>
        <p>You may not use FemRes to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Post hate speech, discriminatory content, or harass others</li>
          <li>Spread false information or misleading content</li>
          <li>Infringe on others' intellectual property or privacy rights</li>
          <li>Engage in spamming or malicious marketing</li>
          <li>Attempt to breach website security or disrupt services</li>
          <li>Create fake accounts or impersonate others</li>
          <li>Upload viruses, malware, or other harmful code</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Content Policy</h2>
        <h3>5.1 Content Standards</h3>
        <p>We encourage content that is:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>High-quality feminist academic resources</li>
          <li>Diverse feminist perspectives and voices</li>
          <li>Constructive discussion and critical thinking</li>
          <li>Inclusive and intersectional feminist content</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.2 Content Moderation</h3>
        <p>We reserve the right to review, edit, or remove content that violates community guidelines. Content moderation is based on:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Community reports and feedback</li>
          <li>AI-assisted content detection</li>
          <li>Manual review processes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <h3>6.1 Platform Intellectual Property</h3>
        <p>The design, features, trademarks, and other intellectual property of the FemRes platform are owned by us.</p>

        <h3>6.2 User Content</h3>
        <p>You retain ownership of content you create, but grant us:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>A non-exclusive license to use, display, and distribute your content</li>
          <li>The right to modify or edit content to provide services</li>
          <li>The right to use your content in promotional materials</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>6.3 Third-Party Content</h3>
        <p>Third-party content on the platform (books, articles, etc.) is owned by their respective owners. We only provide links and descriptions, following fair use principles.</p>

        <h2>7. Privacy</h2>
        <p>Your privacy is important. Please review our <a href="/en/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> to understand how we collect, use, and protect your information.</p>

        <h2>8. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>FemRes provides services "as is." We do not guarantee:</p>
